  "response_text": "Dear [Name],\n\nI was deeply saddened to hear about the loss of your loved one. My heart goes out to you during this incredibly difficult time. Losing someone we love is never easy, and I can only imagine the pain and grief you must be feeling.\n\nPlease know that you are not alone in your sorrow. I want you to know that I am here for you, and I am here to support you in any way I can. If you need someone to talk to, a listening ear, or just a shoulder to cry on, I am here for you.\n\nIt's okay to feel the pain and sadness that comes with losing someone you love. It's okay to grieve and to take the time you need to process your emotions. It's okay to remember the good times, to laugh and to cry, and to cherish the memories you shared with your loved one.\n\nYour loved one may be gone, but their memory and legacy will live on in your heart. They will always be with",
